Khulela Themba Sibiya, Bongani Sandiso Ntanzi, Mthobisi Chris Mncube, Mthokoziseni Zifozonke Mapisa and Sifiso Ntuli are facing charges of murder, attempted murder and robbery. JOHANNESBURG - The case against the five men accused of murdering Senzo Meyiwa has been postponed to 5 March 2021. The five suspects made a brief appearance in court on Friday. UPDATED: Breakthrough in Senzo Meyiwa murder case At their first appearance, four of the five suspects denied involvement in the murder of the late Bafana Bafana goalkeeper. They claim they are being used as scapegoats. Meyiwa was killed six years ago in Vosloorus.